WEBVTT

00:21.041 --> 00:25.416
Every once in a while,
man accomplishes the impossible.

00:26.166 --> 00:29.125
<i>Visual confirm. Landing gear deployed.</i>

00:29.833 --> 00:32.250
<i>Copy that, Columbia.
The Eagle has wings.</i>

00:33.041 --> 00:35.625
All it takes
is someone with a dream.

00:36.291 --> 00:38.250
<i>Godspeed, Eagle.</i>

00:38.250 --> 00:39.666
Because when a man dreams...

00:41.208 --> 00:42.750
...you know what happens.

00:42.750 --> 00:44.958
He can change the world.

00:44.958 --> 00:46.166
All right, cut.

00:47.500 --> 00:50.541
Okay, listen. I don't want
to obstruct your process here,

00:50.541 --> 00:53.458
but I'm looking at the script,
and I'm pretty sure... Yep.

00:53.458 --> 00:56.500
There are zero of those words in it.

00:56.500 --> 00:59.583
True, but only because
the words in the script are dog shit.

00:59.583 --> 01:02.333
All right. Now, look.
Look. Just forget the words.

01:02.333 --> 01:03.750
Ride the truth, buddy.

01:03.750 --> 01:06.666
You're Dr. John Carpenter,
idealistic ghetto physician.

01:06.666 --> 01:10.416
You help everybody: the poor, the sick,
the hungry. You know, blah, blah, blah.

01:10.416 --> 01:12.375
You're Jesus, mate. You're the journey.

01:12.375 --> 01:15.208
Your journey is the journey of America.

01:15.208 --> 01:17.791
And at some point,
you make out with a nun.

01:17.791 --> 01:18.958
Oh, and how good is that?

01:18.958 --> 01:21.000
Yeah. Well, listen up here, rookie.

01:21.000 --> 01:24.166
America doesn't make out with nuns.

01:24.166 --> 01:26.125
Oh yeah?
Well, that's America's loss, isn't it?

01:26.125 --> 01:29.583
All right, listen up.
We're gonna go again. And action!

01:31.958 --> 01:33.458
What the fuck?

01:33.458 --> 01:36.291
Oh come on, people.
What's more important?

01:36.291 --> 01:40.041
Some human buzz cuts
riding a glorified firework to a rock,

01:40.041 --> 01:44.041
or the living art
that we're here making on Earth?

01:46.583 --> 01:48.375
All right, fuck me, let's take five.

01:56.375 --> 01:58.500
<i>Direct from our newsroom in New York,</i>

01:58.500 --> 02:02.041
<i>this is the CBS Evening News
with Walter Cronkite.</i>

02:02.041 --> 02:06.750
<i>The lunar module will descend
to the surface in the next few hours.</i>

02:06.750 --> 02:10.166
<i>The heroism of these men
cannot be overstated.</i>

02:10.166 --> 02:11.958
Oh, will you look at that.

02:11.958 --> 02:16.708
Hmm. Say, you ever get the feeling
we could be doing something more?

02:16.708 --> 02:17.875
- More?
- Yeah.

02:17.875 --> 02:20.375
You know, something,
I don't know... bigger.

02:20.375 --> 02:21.916
Nothing bigger than being Elvis.

02:21.916 --> 02:24.291
I mean, look here.
Right in front of us, right now,

02:24.291 --> 02:28.916
