Oh my God. You should have seen
the look on his grandkids' faces.

15:19.583 --> 15:22.541
And what the hell were his grandkids
doing there? So many questions.

15:23.833 --> 15:25.416
Oh good. You made it back.

15:25.416 --> 15:29.041
So now I guess we're overcompensating
for our moon-landing inadequacies.

15:29.041 --> 15:30.416
Quit it with that crap.

15:30.416 --> 15:31.833
Listen, I get it.

15:31.833 --> 15:34.083
When my mom beat me
in a wet T-shirt contest,

15:34.083 --> 15:36.375
I stopped eating for three months
and burned the bar down.

15:37.791 --> 15:41.625
- Where are we headed?
- There's no "we" happening here.

15:41.625 --> 15:44.416
And you still have mustard on your face.

15:44.416 --> 15:47.416
- Thank you for noticing me. I feel seen.
- You're not getting it.

15:47.416 --> 15:49.541
- Well, at least let me give you a ride.
- No, thanks.

15:49.541 --> 15:52.041
- Oh yeah? You sure about that, big guy?

15:58.625 --> 16:02.833
<i>Shouldn't be long now as we await word
from the valiant crew of Apollo 11</i>

16:02.833 --> 16:04.291
<i>on final descent.</i>

16:04.291 --> 16:06.041
Come on, guys. Get it done.

16:06.041 --> 16:08.083
Yeah, speaking of,
how about we get this done

16:08.083 --> 16:10.541
- and get you back to that set?
- No, the movie can wait.

16:10.541 --> 16:12.833
We're trying to stop
a major drug shipment here.

16:12.833 --> 16:16.250
Yeah, which there are literally
thousands of every fucking day.

16:17.208 --> 16:19.000
Where'd you score this ride, by the way?

16:19.000 --> 16:20.583
It's pretty great, right? Company car.

16:20.583 --> 16:22.333
- Mind if I push these buttons?
- Sure.

16:22.333 --> 16:28.166
Wait. And not get electrocuted or ejected
out of my seat or some other bullshit.

16:28.166 --> 16:30.416
Oh, then, no.
No, I wouldn't touch most of those.

16:31.875 --> 16:33.708
Uh, thank you?

16:33.708 --> 16:35.708
He wants to know if there's any booze.

16:35.708 --> 16:39.000
It's a high-performance, state-of-the-art
intelligence-gathering asset.

16:39.000 --> 16:40.708
It's the third button on your right.

16:45.833 --> 16:48.708
Make that the fourth button
on your right. I think.

16:52.708 --> 16:55.083
Oh my God.
You know we'll never find this guy, right?

16:55.083 --> 16:58.541
Yep. That's why God invented
dickheads with vanity plates.

17:02.750 --> 17:03.583
Hey, buddy.

17:04.166 --> 17:05.375
Need to have a word.

17:09.375 --> 17:10.375
Damn it, Scatter!

17:10.375 --> 17:13.375
- The buttons are not toys!

17:38.083 --> 17:41.041
Looks like you're all out
of foot-chase clichés.

17:41.666 --> 17:43.291
What the hell do you want?

17:43.291 --> 17:44.958
Tell me about the drug shipment.

17:44.958 --> 17:47.625
Shit, man,
Cleopatra shipped out with that yesterday.

17:47.625 --> 17:48.666
Cleopatra?

17:51.041 --> 17:53.666
- Kinda sick of you guys ditching me.

17:53.666 --> 17:56.083
So where's this major
big-time drug shipment anyway?

17:57.458 --> 17:58.750
Already gone.

17:58.750 --> 17:59.791
Oh good.

17:59.791 --> 18:02.500
Okay. So, I guess
that makes this, to quote myself,

18:02.500 --> 18:04.291
"A complete fucking waste of..."

18:07.458 --> 18:08.583
"...time." Damn it.

18:08.583 --> 18:10.791
Uh, sorry.
What was that you were you saying?

18:10.791 --> 18:14.125
Something about you
being completely wrong?

18:15.583 --> 18:16.708
Nice coat.

18:20.791 --> 18:22.125
Cover you? Wait, wait...

18:36.000 --> 18:37.375
Fucking Tuesdays.

18:38.375 --> 18:40.458
We need a plan, all right?
They're getting away.

18:40.458 --> 18:42.125
Here's a plan: who gives a shit?

18:42.125 --> 18:43.750
- Cover me!
- Ah, fuck.

18:43.750 --> 18:45.125
I hate hero time.

18:45.125 --> 18:48.166
For the record, my "Who gives a shit?"
plan was way easier.

19:00.208 --> 19:02.375
<i>Angle down three. Ten feet.</i>

19:06.750 --> 19:10.125
<i>Houston, Tranquility Base here.
The Eagle has landed.</i>

19:15.791 --> 19:16.625
Wait for it.

19:16.625 --> 19:17.625
For what?

19:17.625 --> 19:20.458
You giving away my fucking car?
Already checked that box.

19:20.458 --> 19:24.208
No, I pushed all the buttons
before I dove out.

19:24.208 --> 19:26.750
That car's gonna explode
all over the place.

19:26.750 --> 19:29.041
Wait, you pushed all the buttons?

19:29.041 --> 19:30.583
- Yeah.
- Oh shit.

19:30.583 --> 19:32.541
- What?
- That just locks the doors.

19:33.833 --> 19:36.458
But it did come
with this fun little doohickey

19:36.458 --> 19:38.083
from the Philadelphia office.

19:43.708 --> 19:45.458
- Holy shit.
- Big time.

19:45.458 --> 19:46.375
Where'd it go?

19:46.375 --> 19:48.583
Oh, I don't know.
We haven't figured that out yet.

19:49.583 --> 19:50.833
What's with the dumpy face?

19:50.833 --> 19:52.416
Missed the moon landing.

19:52.416 --> 19:55.000
All right, don't pout.
I'm sure we can get them to do it again.

19:55.000 --> 19:57.208
- What?
-  Just... follow me.

19:57.208 --> 19:59.750
-  Come on. Is anybody out there?

19:59.750 --> 20:03.333
Fuck that fucking monkey
shoving a gun in my fucking dick.

20:03.333 --> 20:05.625
Could this day get any fucking worse?

20:13.291 --> 20:15.708
- Line.
- You don't fucking have one!

20:15.708 --> 20:17.041
Just stand there!

20:17.666 --> 20:20.083
Listen, I didn't
bloody well spend 12 years

20:20.083 --> 20:22.791
getting a PhD in fucking film theory

20:22.791 --> 20:25.291
to be thwarted by a fucking moron, mate!

20:25.291 --> 20:28.625
Oh, I hear you. That sounds frustrating.

20:28.625 --> 20:30.166
- Who's the moron?
- Ugh!

20:30.166 --> 20:32.250
Fuck this. I'm out of here.

20:32.250 --> 20:34.958
Oh God,
did Mary Tyler Moore just say "fuck"?

20:36.083 --> 20:37.916
Officially love her.

20:37.916 --> 20:41.083
Get ready to have your mind
completely fucking blown.

20:43.666 --> 20:47.708
<i>♪ This is Ground Control to Major Tom</i>... <i>♪</i>

20:49.791 --> 20:51.166
Jesus.

20:51.166 --> 20:52.875
Maybe Scatter was right.

20:52.875 --> 20:55.500
What in the hell is this?

20:56.708 --> 20:59.125
This is history in the making.

20:59.791 --> 21:02.125
- Who are you?
- Elvis, I'd like you to meet my boss.

21:02.125 --> 21:04.208
Ooh, been looking forward to meeting you.

21:04.208 --> 21:07.500
Even financed that dogshit movie
next door to get you here.

21:07.500 --> 21:09.208
Had a whole thing planned too.

21:09.208 --> 21:12.333
Drinks, snacks, chocolate volcano,

21:12.333 --> 21:14.666
cuddles, watch the moon landing together,

21:14.666 --> 21:17.875
but a certain somebody was a little late.

21:17.875 --> 21:20.416
Well, yeah,
thanks to his vigilante bullshit.

21:20.416 --> 21:22.916
Also, hi, hello, I didn't know
we had a chocolate volcano.

21:22.916 --> 21:25.000
So, wait a minute.

21:25.000 --> 21:28.708
The moon landing, our finest hour,

21:28.708 --> 21:29.791
you faked it?

21:29.791 --> 21:32.541
Not without help from a cinematic genius.

21:32.541 --> 21:34.416
Say hello to Stanley Kubrick.

21:35.625 --> 21:36.500
Problem, Stan?

21:36.500 --> 21:39.541
Our star seems to be indisposed.

21:39.541 --> 21:40.916
Aw, he in the can?

21:40.916 --> 21:45.125
No. He somehow accidentally
drank a Tang laced with cocaine,

21:45.125 --> 21:46.750
and now he's coked out of his mind

21:46.750 --> 21:49.041
on top of the building
and refuses to come down.

21:49.041 --> 21:50.666
- Damn it, Scatter.
-  What?

21:50.666 --> 21:52.833
- Nothing.
- Well, somebody's gotta wear the suit.

21:52.833 --> 21:54.083
Ah.

21:54.083 --> 21:55.208
Elvis.

21:55.208 --> 21:56.458
- Excuse me?

21:57.458 --> 22:00.083
Hush, hush. Don't worry.
You're about Neil's size.

22:00.750 --> 22:03.250
We've already got the line recorded.
You just have to look pretty.

22:03.250 --> 22:05.916
Hang on a minute. You mean, you want me--

22:05.916 --> 22:08.291
That's right.
Be the first man on the moon.

22:08.291 --> 22:11.041
One small step for man, one...

22:11.958 --> 22:14.583
- Line?
-"Giant leap for mankind."

22:14.583 --> 22:16.791
Shouldn't it be small step for "a" man?

22:16.791 --> 22:18.708
I mean,
if we're gonna be grammatically correct?

22:18.708 --> 22:20.250
- No.
- You know what? Leave it.

22:20.250 --> 22:23.875
Look, someone's gonna figure out
that this isn't real.

22:23.875 --> 22:25.375
We decide what's real.

22:25.375 --> 22:26.750
Which this isn't.

22:26.750 --> 22:28.750
To the world, it is.

22:28.750 --> 22:29.958
You know how I know?

22:29.958 --> 22:32.166
Because Walter Cronkite said so.

22:32.166 --> 22:34.666
Hold on. Is there fucking mayo on this?

22:34.666 --> 22:37.791
Because that would be a national tragedy.

22:37.791 --> 22:41.208
Unless, of course,
you wanna get back to the nuns next door.

22:46.250 --> 22:48.666
<i>That's one small step for man...</i>

22:51.666 --> 22:54.416
<i>one giant leap for mankind.</i>

23:02.333 --> 23:05.625
<i>♪ Ground Control to Major Tom ♪</i>

23:08.750 --> 23:11.000
Welcome to TCB.

23:11.000 --> 23:12.666
<i>♪ ...to Major Tom ♪</i>
